Georg Simmel (pronounced “YORG ZIMMEL”) was born in Berlin in 1858.
One of the first great German sociologists; contemporary of Max Weber (and Ferdinand Tönnies).
An outsider in German academia (anti-Semitism, but baptized Protestant as a child).
Neo-Kantian in his anti-positivistic approach (e.g., “what is society?” much like Kant’s “what is nature?”).
